ial for multidimensional applications, because they only require the flux\nfunction and its Jacobian, which is readily available. Numerical results\nindicate that multiderivative methods are indeed competitive with popular\nstrong stability preserving time integrators.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Apr 2013 00:41:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Aug 2013 04:41:58 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 28 Sep 2013 15:29:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-01"}
