flow wings. These lines are heavily affected by absorption, so that line\nratios of H2O involving the ground states must be treated with caution. The\naverage H2O abundance in high-mass protostellar envelopes does not change much\nwith time. The 987 GHz line appears to be a good tracer of the mean weighted\ndust temperature of the source, which may explain why it is readily seen in\ndistant galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Apr 2013 13:23:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
